            <div class="col-lg-12">
                <div class="advances-intro">
                    <p class="intro-text">Capitalism as an economic system has had and continues to have its share of criticism, blame, and even hatred. While the case for opposing positions toward Capitalism is strong, we cannot rule out that Capitalism, for the most part, actually works better than any other economic system in harnessing the best of man's potential and creating better living standards.</p>
                    <p class="intro-text">However, there is a solid need to advance Capitalism in a way that acknowledges the voices of the critics and embraces the participation of those left out but without hampering the basic principles which make Capitalism effective in fostering innovation and development.</p>
                    <p class="intro-text highlight-text">This very difficult, somewhat oxymoron task has been achieved through the Compassionate Capitalism economic system created by the innovator King Charles N. Lambert. These are some key ways this new system advances Capitalism to a much higher place.</p>
